FBIS3-56064 "drsov009_e_94014" FBIS-SOV-94-009 Document Type:Daily Report 13 Jan 1994 UKRAINE International Affairs Agreement on Crime Prevention Initialed With Israel WS1201132894 Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network in Ukrainian 1100 GMT 12 Jan 94 WS1201132894 Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network Language: Ukrainian Article Type:BFN [Text] According to information from the Center for Public Relations of the Ukrainian Ministry of Internal Affairs, today in the Ukrainian Ministry of Internal Affairs, the Ukrainian minister of internal affairs and Israeli minister of police, energy, and infrastructure initialed an agreement on cooperation in the area of crime prevention and law breaking between the two countries. A news conference for journalists was then held. Answering journalists' questions, Israeli Minister Moshe Shahal stated that Israeli police pay special attention to crime prevention, which is a task for the entire state, not just the police. The use of firearms by criminals, as well as drug smuggling were also discussed.
